**Item #:** ##red|███##-3955

**Object Class:** --Safe-- ##red|Apollyon##

**Special Containment Procedures:** ##red|███##-3955 does not require containment or concealment of any kind##red|, aside from the obligatory warning towards all staff involved in the official ███ Foundation CAOCIT[[footnote]] Cyclical Analysis Over Countably Infinite Time [[/footnote]] program to cease all testing involving musical or harmonic analysis.##

##red|The [*http://www.scpwiki.com/domc-hub ██████████ of █████████████████] is in charge of upkeep of this document's adherence to internally recognized regulations. All unauthorized changes are to be reverted immediately, and all updates are to be brought to ██████ ████ for manual review.##

**Description:** ##red|███##-3955 is an eight note melody of relative pitches. These pitches may vary based on the key of the root note, but contain no additional pitches separating the main eight notes[[footnote]] With the exception of sequences of each note appearing in tandem uniformly. [[/footnote]]. Because of the layout of a standard musical octave, there are twelve iterations of ##red|███##-3955, each beginning on a different root pitch, and updating the following pitches relative to the starting note. An example of ##red|███##-3955, beginning on F, has been provided below.

[[include :snippets:html5player
|type=audio
|url=http://smlt.wikidot.com//local--files/henzoid:aimusic/anomalouschords_0.mp3
]]

##red|███##-3955 does not possess any anomalous properties, but is rather the byproduct of an anomalous phenomenon, which can be defined as follows: As time increases, the likelihood that an AI with the goal of creating music will produce something involving ##red|███##-3955 asymptotically approaches one. That is to say, after extreme lengths of time, it is nearly guaranteed that every piece of music produced by a given AI will contain ##red|███##-3955. The collective notes contained within ##red|███##-3955 do not fall into any commonly recognized scale[[footnote]] Some versions of a Spanish Eight Tone Scale can be adapted to contain the notes of ##red|███##-3955. [[/footnote]], and its inclusion is almost always as the bass line of the chord progression, rather than the actual melody. 

